.SH NAME
hscolour \- colourise Haskell code
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B hscolour
.RI [ options ] " file.hs"
.SH DESCRIPTION
Colourises Haskell code. Currently five output formats are supported:
ANSI terminal codes, HTML 3.2 with <font> tags, HTML 4.01 with CSS,
LaTeX, and mIRC chat client codes.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-oOUTPUT
.TP
.B \-html
Set output to HTML 3.2
.TP
.B \-css
Set output to HTML 4.01 with CSS format
.TP
.B \-tty
Set output to ANSI terminal codes
.TP
.B \-latex
Set output to LaTeX format
.TP
.B \-mirc
Set output to mIRC format
.TP
.B \-lit, \-nolit
Turn on/off skipping of literate parts
.TP
.B \-anchor, \-noanchor
Turn on/off creation of anchors
.TP
.B \-partial, -nopartial
Turn header on/off
.TP
.B \-help
Display usage summary
.TP
.B \-version
Display version
